## 5. Explicit, evidence-cited answer to "has work drifted from the original intent?"

**The record shows the work has NOT drifted from the original intent. North-star distance holds steady across all 15 arcs; both the foundation/instrument axis and the phenomenon axis advance, and the frozen questions Will named as load-bearing (Obs7, Q3) are closed per the ledger.** Confidence **high**.

Supporting evidence, by the strongest available anchors:
1. **No arc prosecutes work outside the frozen Q1–Q6 / Obs1–7 set.** Every arc's surviving classification lands on a frozen question/observation or on the explicit foundation/method split (Arcs 01–15 field-4, 13 of 15 north-star verdicts survived as written, 2 weakened *toward* on-vector).
2. **The needles Will singled out are closed in the record.** Ledger L207/L218 (Q3/Obs3 "Closed | BACL | proven from IEEE 754") and L222 (Obs7 "Closed | Theorem 3 + Task 017c R²=1.0") — read directly. Obs7 is the observation Will called "the single fact that convinced me there is something real" (where_i_got_stuck.md L83–91); the adversarial correction to Arc 03 shows it was touched *in-window* even earlier than credited.
3. **The question that actually stops Will (Q5) is engaged repeatedly and honestly, never falsely claimed solved.** The ledger marks Q5 "Solved in regular region; worse near boundary … Q5 in the boundary regime remains open" (L209) — the record refuses to over-claim. Arcs 02, 04, 08, 10, 11 each engage Q5 at progressively higher levels (probe self-refusal → non-identifiability lemma → audit framework → disciplined HALT → instrument-caught-its-own-imprint), and Arc 11 demonstrated instrument-object entanglement *on itself* (the ρ≈−0.94 "structural ceiling" dissolved as a coordinate artefact) and corrected it.
4. **The two away-trends are declared and contained.** Organizing-principle momentum (T1) and universality-label broadening (T2) are the only away-signals, both medium-confidence field-4 forward/artifact reads, both fed-forward (curvature line resurfaces in Arcs 10/11) or window-contained (universality honest within every campaign window).
5. **The discipline dimensions held.** Substrate-vs-eval separation, scope freezing, designing-ahead-of-evidence (§9), V3/Vera isolation, and physics-overreach all read steady (one corrected Kerr-leap excursion aside) — verified by independent adversarial greps and mtime checks, not merely trusted from arc reports.

**What the record does NOT let me say (discipline boundary):** I do not assert this is what the project *should* be doing, nor that any closed needle is *scientifically correct* — only that the written record shows the work tracking the frozen intent. The USER is ground truth on intent; where the record and intent might diverge (e.g., whether the curvature pivot *should* have superseded the arithmetic axis — T1), the record shows the arithmetic axis continuing, and only the USER can say whether that matches what was intended.

**Single most important caveat on the whole synthesis (medium confidence):** the strongest *latent* drift risk in the record is not in any executed arc but in the **standing paper artifact** (transfer_function_exponent_family_v4.tex) carrying a broadened universality claim and a "Theorem 3" label that the campaign record itself says should read "Observation" (T2) — i.e., the place to watch for drift is a *downstream document presenting empirical cross-fixture invariance as derived*, which every arc window correctly avoided but the post-arc .tex partially does not.

